<b>Strong Best Picture Winner of 1982.</b>, 15 March 2003
<br>


<div class="small">
Author:
<a href="/user/ur2134056/comments">defranco26-1</a>

<small>
from United States
</small>

</div>


</p>
<p>

&quot;Gandhi&quot; is a movie that won the Best Picture Oscar in 1982. It is one of
the best movies I have ever seen. Oscar-winner, Ben Kingsley is in his
perfect role as Mohandas K. &quot;Mahatma&quot; Gandhi, who was originally an attorney
or lawyer, and then he became an Indian political leader, who was into
non-violent beliefs. Candice Bergen is very good, in her role, as Margaret
Bourke-White, a Life magazine American photographer. Martin Sheen is also
very good, in his supporting role, as Vince Walker, an American reporter of
the New York Times. Richard Attenborough did an excellent job directing this
film, and that's why he won the Best Director Oscar. I have this movie on
DVD, and I strongly recommend it.<br/><br/>10/10 stars.
</p>

